<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 7:30PM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern
Sequatchie, southern Marion and Hamilton Counties through 900 PM
EDT/800 PM CDT/...
At 830 PM EDT/730 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles north of Fairmount
to near Signal Mountain to near South Pittsburg. Movement was east at
35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Jasper, Soddy-Daisy, Signal Mountain, South Pittsburg,
Walden, Lakesite, Kimball, Ridgeside and Fairmount.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
